    <!-- Nydri, Greece Dropdown -->
    <section class="destination-section">
        <a class="anchor" id="nydri"></a>
        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Nydri, Greece</h2>
        <p>Lastly, you can visit the port city of <strong>Nydri</strong> and take in amazing views over the surrounding picturesque landscape, which is best admired from alongside the harbor, or ideally from a boat.</p>
        <p>If you have more time, you might consider the hike to the nearby <strong>Nidri Waterfalls</strong>, which can be reached with a 0.8 mile (1.3 km) round-trip hike through a scenic canyon gorge.</p>
        <p>You can also head up into the <strong>Nydri Hills</strong> above Nydri and Rachi to take in breathtaking views over the many neighboring Ionian Islands, with views stretching to the mainland on a clear day. One of the best viewpoints can be found near the Villa Maura hotel, with various perspectives offered along the road.</p>
        <p>There's also the possibility of taking a boat tour from Nydri along the island's southern rugged coastline, stopping at several beaches including Porto Katsiki along the way and taking in views of Cape Lefkada from the sea.</p>
    </section>



